{{Infobox product | image = [[File:LG Smart DIOS V9100.jpg|150px]] | type = [[Internet refrigerator]] | inventor = | inception = June 2000 | manufacturer = [[LG Electronics]] | available = | url = }}
The '''LG Internet Digital DIOS''' (also known as '''R-S73CT''') is an [[internet refrigerator]] released by [[LG Electronics]] in June 2000. The technology is the result of a project that started in 1997 and staffed by a team of 55 researchers with a budget cost of Won15 bil (US$49.2 million).
==Features== The refrigerator has a TFT-LCD (thin-film transistor-liquid crystal display) screen with TV functionality and Local Area Network (LAN) port. It includes a LCD information window that features electronic pen, data memo, video messaging and schedule management functions and provides information, such as inside temperature, the freshness of stored foods, nutrition information and recipes. Other features are a webcam that is used as a scanner and tracks what is inside the refrigerator, a MP3 player and a three-level automatic icemaker. In addition, the electricity consumption is half the level of conventional refrigerators and the noise level is only 23 decibels.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telecompaper.com/news/lg-unveils-internetready-refrigerator--221266|title=LG UNVEILS INTERNET-READY REFRIGERATOR|work=LG Electronics|publisher=telecompaper.com|date=June 21, 2000|accessdate=October 11, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=99743|title=No need for PCs with intelligent fridges|work=[[ITWeb]]|date=December 13, 2000|accessdate=October 11, 2014}}</ref>
